4. Datasheet
We propose a comprehensive datasheet template tailored for soft robotics, providing a structured overview of the discussed material parameters. In many cases, manufacturers do not report all relevant information, such as complete stress–strain curves or hyperelastic model parameters. This lack of information complicates the creation of accurate material models and often leads to repetition of experiments across research groups. By standardizing the presentation of key properties, this datasheet not only addresses these gaps but also promotes reproducibility, transparency, and data sharing in the soft robotics community. As illustrated in Figure 6 for Dragon Skin 30, the datasheet is divided into several sections. Header information: Lists the material’s manufacturer, the author of the datasheet, the elastomer category (e.g., thermoplastic, thermosetting), and a DOI or link to the dataset containing all measurement data. Material properties: The central table summarizes the most important material parameters for soft robotics as discussed in Section 3, alongside the standard test method used (if any).
